10 February 2021 Mortdale RSL 25 Macquarie Place , Mortdale
Do you find checking your blood glucose painful, or are you unsure what your
results mean? This practical session will teach you the importance of
monitoring your blood glucose levels (BGLs) and understanding your results.
You’ll be given practical tips for effective testing and keeping your BGLs
* The effects of blood glucose on your body
* How to test and self-manage your BGLs
* Setting goals to improve diabetes management and prevent future complications.
Please bring your own blood glucose testing kit (meter, strips, lancet) for a
 _This program is for people living with type 2 diabetes._
